---
title: Birria Tacos
source: Rick Martínez, NYT Cooking (adapted)
servings: 8
prep time: 30 min
cook time: 3 hours
tags:
  - mexican
  - tacos
  - birria
  - braised
---

= Chili Sauce

Toast @guajillo chiles{6}(stemmed, seeded) and @ancho chiles{4}(stemmed, seeded)
in a dry #skillet{} for ~{1%minute} per side until fragrant and pliable.

Transfer to a #bowl{} and cover with boiling water. Soak for ~soak chiles{20%minutes}.

Drain and blend with @roasted tomatoes{14%oz}(canned), @white onion{1/2}(roughly chopped),
@garlic{4%cloves}, @apple cider vinegar{2%tbsp}, @dried oregano{1%tsp},
@ground cumin{1%tsp}, @ground cloves{1/4%tsp}, @black pepper{1/2%tsp},
and @salt{1%tsp} in a #blender{} until very smooth.

= Braise

Preheat #oven to 325°F.

Season @beef chuck{3%lbs}(cut into 2-inch chunks) generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Sear in @vegetable oil{2%tbsp} in a #dutch oven{} over high heat for
~{3-4%minutes} per side until deeply browned. Work in batches.

Pour the chili sauce over the beef. Add @beef broth{2%cups} and @bay leaves{2}.

Cover and braise in the oven for ~braise{2.5-3%hours} until fork-tender.

= Assemble

Shred the beef. Strain and reserve the consommé (the braising liquid).

Dip @corn tortillas{16} in the consommé, then griddle in a #comal{} or
#cast iron skillet{} with a bit of the fat from the consommé until crispy,
about ~{2%minutes} per side.

Fill with shredded birria, @white onion{1/2}(diced), @cilantro{1/2%cup}(chopped),
and @lime{2}(wedges).

Serve with a bowl of hot consommé for dipping.
